        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-05-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-05-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="491" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d491">
                <head>Municipal Council of Leith</head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Leith</placeName>, <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian" when="1865-05-02">May 2, 1865</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>At Leith, the second day of May, one thousand eight hundred and sixty-five,
                        which day the honorable the provost magistrates and council of the borough
                        of Leith being assembled, unanimously resolved to record their abhorrence of
                        the atrocious assassination of President Lincoln of the United States of
                        America, and their deepest sympathy with the people of the United States
                        under the calamity which has befallen them.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Extracted from the council records by—</salute>
                    <signed>H. H. COUPER, </signed>
                    <hi rend="italic">Town Clerk</hi>.</closer>
            </div>
